---
description: Backend routes/services structure rules
globs:
  - "backend/src/**"
---

Keep backend responsibilities separated.

Preferred structure:

- `backend/src/index.ts`: app setup, middleware, route registration, WS registration.
- `backend/src/routes/**`: HTTP routing, request parsing, validation, response shape.
- `backend/src/services/**`: business logic, LLM clients, external integrations.
- `backend/src/ws/**`: WebSocket state, command handling, broadcast/replay logic.
- `backend/src/db.ts`: lowdb initialization and persistence access.
- `backend/src/http/**`: HTTP helpers such as validation responses.

Rules:

- Do not put large business logic directly in `index.ts`.
- Do not mix WebSocket state into HTTP route files unless the route is explicitly
  about exposing on-air state.
- Validate incoming data before writing to lowdb.
- Use shared schemas for API/WS/LLM contracts when available.
- Keep external systems behind services/adapters.
- Avoid adding a new persistence layer for MVP unless Karen explicitly asks.
- Keep route responses predictable JSON.

If a route starts doing more than validation and orchestration, move logic into
a service.
